eNCA's Aviwe Mtila reports. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Tensions are rising again in Rabie Ridge near Tembisa as people erect homes on government land. Nearly two weeks ago, private security opened fire on land invaders who were burning tires and protesting. READ: Rabie Ridge | The land is not ours - Gauteng govt Residents say the government promised them RDP houses. They have also complained of the slow pace of construction of affordable housing and claim the money for the construction has been misappropriated.